The paper focuses on the functioning of gossip networks underlying cryptocurrencies, which involves topics such as data transfer, storage, and message passing protocols. This suggests that the paper could belong to the categories of computer security (cs.CR), distributed computing (cs.DC), networked information systems (cs.NI), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), and social and information networks (cs.SI). However, given the emphasis on vulnerabilities and financial implications, cs.CR is the most likely category, followed by cs.DC and cs.NI.
